[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Zechariah 8:16-17. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Zechariah 8:16-17",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "These are the things that ye shall do, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — But these my promises of good to you are conditional, and the performance of them will depend upon your observing the laws of justice and righteousness; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Speak ye every man the truth to his neighbour — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Let no one deceive another by guile or falsehood. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Execute the judgment of truth — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "True judgment; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and peace in your gates — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Use all means to restore and establish peace among you. Or, Let those who have the administration of justice committed to their charge endeavour to search out the truth from the witnesses, in the trials which come before them; and decide according to the law, and do all in their power to uphold truth and integrity, and maintain the public peace. The judges, it is to be remembered, used to execute their office at the gates of each city, and therefore it is said here, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Execute judgments, &c., in your gates. Let none of you imagine evil in your hearts — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See note on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Zechariah 7:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And love no false oath — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See note on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Zechariah 5:3-4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For all these are things which I hate — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "God, as he essentially, by his nature, loves that which is good and excellent, so must he hate that which is the contrary.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "8:9-17 Those only who lay their hands to the plough of duty, shall have them strengthened with the promises of mercy: those who avoid their fathers' faults have the curse turned into a blessing. Those who believed the promises, were to show their faith by their works, and to wait the fulfilment. When God is displeased, he can cause trade to decay, and set every man against his neighbour; but when he returns in mercy, all is happy and prosperous. Surely believers in Christ must not trifle with the exhortation to put away lying, and to speak every man peace with his neighbour, to hate what the Lord hates, and to love that wherein he delights.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "These are the things that ye shall do - He exhorts them to the same duties, to which the former prophets had exhorted their fathers, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Zechariah 7:9-10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and, as before, first positively to truth and peace; then to avoid everything contrary to it. \"Judgment of peace\" must be judgment which issues in peace, as all righteous judgment righteously received, in which case each party acquiesces, must. Kimchi: \"If ye judge righteousness, there will be peace between the litigants, according to that proverb, Sanhedr. f. 7. a. quoted by Me. Caul, p. 78), 'He that hath his coat taken from him by the tribunal, let him sing and go his way' (\"because,\" says a gloss (Rashi, quoted Ibid.), \"they have judged the judgment of truth, and have taken away that which would have been stolen property, if he retained it,\" being in fact not his). And they have quoted that, \"And all this people shall go to their place in peace\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 18:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". : \"All this people,\" even he that is condemned in judgment. It is also interpreted of arbitration. What sort of judgment is that, in which there is peace? It is that of arbitration.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "16, 17. The promised blessings are connected with obedience. God's covenanted grace will lead those truly blessed by it to holiness, not licentiousness.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "truth to … neighbour—not that the truth should not be spoken to foreigners too; but He makes it an aggravation of their sin, that they spared not even their brethren. Besides, and above all outward ordinances (Zec 7:3), God requires truth and justice.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "judgment of … peace—Equitable decisions tend to allay feuds and produce peace.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "gates—the place where courts of judicature in the East were held.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
