  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "These are the things that ye shall do,.... Which were duties incumbent on them, and which it became them to perform, under a sense of the favours bestowed on them, to show their gratitude to God, and that they might glorify him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Speak ye every man the truth to his neighbour; not using deceit, prevarication, and lying, Ephesians 4:25 and it becomes every man under the Gospel dispensation, according to the gift he has received, to speak, publish, and declare the truth of the Gospel, to the edification of others: ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Speak ye every man the truth to his neighbour; not using deceit, prevarication, and lying, ",
            "children": []
